WEBVTT

00:00.044 --> 00:01.483
Previously on The O.C....

00:01.484 --> 00:03.661
Summer, I like you this much.

00:03.662 --> 00:05.156
God, how did I not get in?

00:05.157 --> 00:06.412
- Why are you lying about it?
- I got in!

00:06.413 --> 00:08.935
She said if I didn't get in and she did, she wouldn't go to Brown.

00:08.936 --> 00:11.265
We applied to Brown so that we could be together.

00:11.266 --> 00:12.485
I guess I changed my mind.

00:12.486 --> 00:13.178
We're over.

00:13.179 --> 00:15.957
I keep trying to picture myself at Berkeley. I can't.

00:15.958 --> 00:17.354
Check out Newport Barbie.

00:17.352 --> 00:18.952
How about $700 million?

00:18.951 --> 00:20.066
Now you're trying to bribe me.

00:20.063 --> 00:21.099
You've got to get him to quit this.

00:21.099 --> 00:22.690
I can't just quit.

00:23.463 --> 00:24.544
I went to see your mother.

00:24.545 --> 00:26.715
All you have to do is go to your son's birthday.

00:26.716 --> 00:27.419
I don't know.

00:27.420 --> 00:30.484
She wanted to make it here but she... she couldn't.

00:34.991 --> 00:37.997
Nice job on the grill, Seth. Those swordfish look perfect.

00:37.998 --> 00:42.109
Wow, the student becomes a master. There's a new king of the B-B-Q.

00:42.110 --> 00:43.450
I cede you my oven mitts.

00:43.451 --> 00:46.141
And here I thought I was destined to live in your shadow.

00:46.152 --> 00:48.621
See, buddy? No need to become a fisherman after all.

00:48.622 --> 00:50.397
Yeah, that was a bad idea.

00:50.398 --> 00:51.796
We all have our moments.

00:51.797 --> 00:54.549
You mean like you lying to Summer and breaking up with her to cover it up?

00:54.550 --> 00:56.336
No, actually, I think that was a great idea.

00:56.337 --> 00:58.695
Yeah, 'cause what was your other option: telling her the truth?

00:58.696 --> 01:00.147
- Exactly.
- Yeah.

01:00.148 --> 01:01.200
What are you guys talking about?

01:01.201 --> 01:02.675
- Nothing.
- Nothing.

01:03.029 --> 01:05.961
Ryan, I don't know if you saw, but your graduation tickets came.

01:05.962 --> 01:07.875
Aisle seats. Nice!

01:07.876 --> 01:09.690
Although you'd think after sending two kids to Harbor,

01:09.691 --> 01:12.138
they could cough up more than two tickets per student.

01:12.139 --> 01:13.862
He's just worried about the Nana.

01:13.863 --> 01:15.439
Well, she is an excellent clapper.

01:15.440 --> 01:17.033
She can do the two-finger whistle.

01:17.034 --> 01:19.051
She's never taken a picture out of focus.

01:19.052 --> 01:21.043
The woman was born for graduations.

01:21.044 --> 01:22.951
Well, let her take my tickets.

01:23.660 --> 01:26.163
I mean, Seth's got you guys covered.

01:26.164 --> 01:28.284
I'd hate to see mine go to waste.

01:29.140 --> 01:31.515
Why don't you invite someone from your family?

01:31.869 --> 01:33.842
Your mom would love it.

01:38.546 --> 01:40.192
I'm going to go wash up.

01:40.850 --> 01:43.218
Sink's right here, uh...

01:43.219 --> 01:45.971
I don't think it's such a good idea, honey. I tried this already.

01:45.972 --> 01:48.465
She signed up for AA. She's starting her life again.

01:48.466 --> 01:52.161
Yeah, after writing bad checks and getting arrested and disappearing.

01:52.162 --> 01:53.817
She doesn't have the greatest track record.

01:53.818 --> 01:55.528
I think I'm going to wash up, too.

01:57.408 --> 01:58.687
It's important to him.

01:58.688 --> 02:00.609
I just don't want to see him get hurt again.

02:00.610 --> 02:03.263
- It's his decision.
- Well, he's still a kid.

02:03.264 --> 02:07.313
Right. Because when we get older, we make much better decisions.

